The rate of concussions per 1,000 plays decreased from 10.93 to 2.04 in the Ivy League

following an experimental kickoff rule change in 2016

From 2013 to 2015, kickoffs made up six percent of all plays but 21 percent of all concussions—26 out of 126 total. A 2016 rule that moved the

kickoff line from the 35-yard line to the 40-yard line saw a dramatic reduction in the occurrence of concussions during kickoff plays, with kickoffs

making up a similar proportion of total plays but only nine percent of concussions.

After the rule change (2016-2017)
